Nested Loop :- A loop inside a loop is called Nested loop .

For every problem there will be thrre type of solution 
Brute force
Better 
Optimal

Most of the brute solutions will get using tools and most of the solutions will be solving using tools .

ex:-
public class Main
{
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		for (int i = 1; i<=5;i++){
		    for(int j = 1;j<=5;j++){
		        
		    }
		}
	}
}


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Pattern Printing :-
Step 1 :- Print no.of rows.
Step 2 :- Print no.of columns.
Step 3 :- Print what to print and what not to print.

ex:-

public class Main
{
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		for (int i = 1; i<=5;i++){
		    for(int j = 1;j<=5;j++){
		        System.out.print("*");
		        
		    }
		    System.out.println();
		}
	}
}



public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int size = 5; 

        for (int row = 0; row < size; row++) {
            for (int col = 0; col < size; col++) {
                if (row == 0 || row == size - 1 || col == 0 || col == size - 1) {
                    System.out.print("* ");
                } else {
                    System.out.print("  ");
                }
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}




